The National Coordinator of Community and Social Development Project, Dr. Abdulkarim Obaje, has disclosed that CSO has completed over 11,000 micro projects in rural areas across the country. He disclosed this in a chat with Daily Trust at Iloko-Ijesa, Osun State on Friday shortly after the quarterly review of the activities of CSDP nationwide. He said the people of the communities should take ownership of projects in their communities and tasked government at all levels to adopt the community-driven development model in the rural areas. He appealed to those at the elms of affairs of government to adopt people-oriented model and put the rural people in the driving seat of their community's development. He called for the institutionalisation of community-driven development model in the country.